Ann B. Cairns | Eckert Seamans




































Menu











Ann  B. Cairns

							Member
						





Overview




Representative Matters




Professional Affiliations






Overview
Ann Cairns is a member in the firm’s Professional Liability Group and focuses her practice on the defense of professional malpractice claims, complex insurance coverage issues, and appellate practice. She specializes in complex medical malpractice cases involving catastrophic injuries with a high level of monetary exposure. She also has extensive experience in psychiatric malpractice cases, cases brought under the federal Emergency Medical Treatment and Labor Act (EMTALA), and cases involving allegations of sexual molestation brought against health care providers.
Prior to becoming an attorney, Ann was an occupational therapist who held management positions, including clinical coordinator of the Head Trauma Rehabilitation Program at Sunrise Rehabilitation Hospital in Sunrise, Florida, and assistant chief of occupational therapy at Thomas Jefferson University Hospital. While working in the health care field, Ann served as an expert witness, testifying in court in personal injury cases involving patients with traumatic head injuries. Ann’s health care background and her experience as an expert witness are valuable assets to the defense of health care providers and organizations.


Representative Matters

Defense of complex medical malpractice claims involving catastrophic injuries.
Represents hospitals, physicians, and other health care providers in disputes concerning privileging, credentialing, and licensure.
Represents hospitals with respect to issues of guardianship and consent to medical and psychiatric treatment.
Represents hospitals in claims involving negligent hiring, supervision, and retention.



Professional Affiliations

